00:37.872 --> 00:39.208
He finally stopped fussing.

00:39.233 --> 00:40.506
You were right.

00:40.531 --> 00:42.920
A stroll around the
pond was all he needed.

00:43.096 --> 00:45.308
Ah, such a handful last night.

00:45.333 --> 00:47.227
Nothing I did would calm him down.

00:47.252 --> 00:49.009
You must be exhausted.

00:49.034 --> 00:51.470
Well, Rosemary came over
when she heard him crying

00:51.495 --> 00:53.531
and then before long Lee came over, too.

00:53.556 --> 00:55.182
We took turns napping.

00:56.044 --> 00:57.764
I would like to have you
and Rosemary and Lee

00:57.789 --> 00:59.024
over for dinner.

00:59.049 --> 01:01.785
My way of saying thank you for
everything you've done for us.

01:01.819 --> 01:03.621
Oh, that sounds lovely.

01:03.653 --> 01:05.155
Well, how is the little man doing?

01:05.188 --> 01:06.650
He's doing great.

01:08.391 --> 01:09.879
So are you heading somewhere?

01:09.904 --> 01:11.073
Yeah, Cape Fullerton.

01:11.098 --> 01:12.499
They've called me in
as an expert witness

01:12.524 --> 01:13.926
on this gunrunner trial.

01:13.951 --> 01:16.577
A couple of bad guys from
the Northern Territories.

01:17.162 --> 01:19.914
Well, hopefully they end
up behind bars forever.

01:20.039 --> 01:21.008
They will.

01:21.033 --> 01:22.750
It's an air-tight case.

01:23.371 --> 01:25.915
Elizabeth, you should be proud.

01:25.940 --> 01:27.656
Jack chased these guys for a long time.

01:27.681 --> 01:28.336
Yeah.

01:28.361 --> 01:29.799
His work is finally paying off.

01:29.824 --> 01:31.802
I'm just glad it's coming to an end.

01:32.507 --> 01:33.345
Be safe.

01:33.370 --> 01:34.597
Thanks.

01:37.838 --> 01:39.430
It is outrageous!

01:39.455 --> 01:40.222
I mean, what does he think this is,

01:40.247 --> 01:41.182
Union City?

01:41.207 --> 01:42.376
No, I agree.

01:42.401 --> 01:44.647
Something needs to be done about this.

01:45.341 --> 01:46.425
What's wrong?

01:46.450 --> 01:48.786
It's that Lucas Bouchard.

01:48.976 --> 01:50.844
Have you noticed what's been
happening at the saloon?

01:50.869 --> 01:53.405
I have put up with his
remodelling during the day,

01:53.430 --> 01:54.756
but that noise?

01:54.781 --> 01:55.767
At night?

01:55.792 --> 01:57.826
At 11:00 I could hear it at my house.

01:57.851 --> 01:59.115
Yes, we heard it too.

01:59.147 --> 02:00.602
It woke up poor Cody.

02:00.627 --> 02:02.362
This isn't how Tom ran the saloon.

02:02.387 --> 02:04.388
And the music he plays.

02:04.413 --> 02:06.984
It is quite provocative.

02:07.009 --> 02:08.077
Mmmhmm.

02:08.237 --> 02:11.133
So, what're we gonna do about it?

02:40.863 --> 02:45.347
